Seriki Adinoyi in Jos At least 24 persons have again been killed in a night attack on Dundu village of Kwal district of Bassa local government area of Plateau state. Confirming the attack, President of Irigwe Devt Association (IDA), Hon Sunday Abdu, said the suspected Fulani attackers swooped on the community last night and raided in for hours, leaving at least 24 persons dead in the aftermath. Police Public Relation Officer (PPRO), Mr Tyopev Terna, who also confirmed the attack, could not give details. He said a Deputy Commissioner of Police from the command has gone to the scene, and shall give details on return. Kwal is the village where the headquarters of Nigerian College of Accountancy (NCA) is located. Details later……